Reasoning: The paper deals with distributed channel access in multi-hop cognitive radio networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), machine learning (cs.LG), control systems (cs.SY), and multimedia (cs.MM). The use of multi-armed bandits and maximum weighted independent set (MWIS) also suggests a connection to algorithms (cs.DS) and optimization (cs.DM), but these are less likely given the focus on wireless networks.
